Title: Post-Quantum Fiat-Shamir
Time: 14:00, Sep 16
Venue:SEIEE3-404
Host: Yu Yu
Abstract:
The Fiat-Shamir transformation is a useful
approach to building non-interactive arguments (of
knowledge) in the random oracle model. Unfortunately,
existing proof techniques are incapable of proving the
security of Fiat-Shamir in the quantum setting. The
problem stems from (1) the diffculty of quantum rewinding, and (2) the inability of
current techniques to adaptively program random oracles in the quantum setting.
In this talk, I will talk about how to overcome the limitations above in many
settings. And as an application, I will show existing lattice signatures based or
Fiat-Shamir are secure without any modifications.
Bio:
Qipeng Liu is a Ph.D student in Computer Science Department, Princeton
University. He is advised by Professor Mark Zhandry. His research focuses on
post-quantum cryptography,quantum random oracle model and he also has broad
interest in cryptography. Before becoming a Ph.D student in Princeton University,
he received his bachelor in IlIS, Tsinghua University.
